
In a MERN stack backend project (Node.js with Express), a .gitignore file helps you exclude unnecessary or sensitive files. Here's a typical .gitignore for a MERN backend:

gitignore
Copy code
# Node.js dependencies
node_modules/

# Logs
logs/
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*

# Environment variables
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local

# Runtime data
pids/
*.pid
*.seed
*.pid.lock

# OS-specific files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# IDE-specific files
.vscode/
.idea/
*.suo
*.ntvs*
*.njsproj
*.sln

# Testing
coverage/

# Build output
dist/
build/

# Temporary files
tmp/
temp/

# Other
*.swp